definitions.definition: The act of impelling or driving onward , or the state of being impelled ; the sudden or momentary agency of a body in motion on another body; also, the impelling force, or impulse.
Influence acting unexpectedly or temporarily on the mind ; sudden motive or influence ; impulse .
